<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - SPECIAL TORQUES - VALVE LEVER POST
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="3">
        <title>VALVE LEVER POST</title>
        <para>Engine Crankshaft Vibration Damper Timing Mark Positioned at 11:00 o'clock (20&#176; from Vertical) for
            Valve Lever Post Bolt Torque (Damper Behind Pulley).
        </para>
        <para>Rotate engine until timing mark (notch) on vibration damper is at 11:00 (20&#176; before vertical). This
            positions all pistons below TDC so the valves do not, contact the pistons when tightening the valve lever
            assemblies (
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350305">3.5</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            ).
        </para>
        <para>Tighten each pair of valve lever post bolts down
            <emph type="underscr">EVENLY</emph>
            to 20 lb-ft. (27 Nm) (
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350306">3.6</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            ).
        </para>
        <figure id="ef4350304" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="cg9841" filename="../figcg9/CG9841.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 3.4 Valve Cover Torque Sequence</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="ef4350305" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="cg10309" filename="../figcg1/CG10309.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 3.5 Engine Crankshaft Vibration Damper Timing Mark Positioned at 11:00 (20&#176; from
                Vertical) for Valve Lever Post Bolt Torque (Damper Behind Pulley)
            </caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="ef4350306" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="cg11056" filename="../figcg1/CG11056.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 3.6 Valve Lever (Rocker Arm) Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
